parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Battery Drain and Electrical System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the battery to drain, leaving the driver stranded, which can lead to safety risks, especially in remote areas.
symptoms: The battery is dead or drains quickly
the vehicle won't start
the rear lift gate or trunk won't open
the radio or other electrical components malfunction
and the battery warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Lift Gate and Trunk Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the rear lift gate and trunk can cause the battery to drain, leading to safety risks, and make it difficult to access the cargo area.
symptoms: The rear lift gate or trunk won't open
the battery drains quickly
the vehicle won't start
and the hatch sensor beeps repeatedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of electrical system components, such as the battery, starter, and alternator, can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle won't start
the battery is dead
the starter or alternator malfunctions
and the electrical system drains the battery.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to address recall issues, such as the electrical system recall, can lead to safety risks and battery drain.
symptoms: The vehicle is included in a recall
but the part is unavailable
or the manufacturer has exceeded a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or hesitate while accelerating, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power while driving
hesitates when accelerating
jerks or slips when shifting gears
and may produce a grinding sound.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The issues with the Continuously Variable Transmission (CVT) can cause the vehicle to hesitate, jerk, or slip when shifting gears, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or jerks when shifting gears
slips or fails to engage when accelerating
and may produce a grinding sound.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing the transmission and CVT issues can lead to continued safety risks and inconvenience to the driver.
symptoms: The driver receives notification of a recall
but the parts are not available
or the repair is delayed
leaving the vehicle in an unsafe condition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected cracking of the windshield can obstruct the driver's view, leading to accidents or other safety hazards.
symptoms: Windshield cracks or shatters without apparent cause
cracks spread rapidly
cracks appear after washing or exposure to temperature changes
cracks originate from the bottom or edge of the windshield.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected cracking or shattering of the sunroof glass can cause injury or distraction to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Sunroof glass cracks or shatters without apparent cause
cracks appear after washing or exposure to temperature changes
water leaks into the vehicle through the sunroof.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water leaks into the vehicle through the sunroof can cause damage to the interior, electrical systems, and create an environment conducive to mold growth.
symptoms: Water leaks into the vehicle through the sunroof
water accumulates in the C-pillar and floorboard
mold and mildew growth in the vehicle.
